          : 'the propagation chain is not "JavaScript vs Python vs R" as parallel ecosystems — it is one tree rooted at GDAL/PROJ/GEOS (C++) with language bindings as branches. Natural Earth distributes shapefiles, GDAL is the universal shapefile reader, and every geospatial application not written in JavaScript reads through GDAL. Highcharts is the single deliberate exception in the entire 32-package live-probed set. Existence proof that overriding is technically possible — and an editorial decision that ~99% of the ecosystem has declined to make.'
